                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2002-12-18</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>Of all the books I have on boat design, this is my favorite. It is also the most easily understood, the cheapest, and the only one that came with big sets of plans.<P>This book is a great deal. Not only is it filled with all the information you need to go out to your garage/yard/shed and build a boat, it also, gives you the basics for sail, power, and rowing and the plans to do it. All the info, plans for 6 boats, and Jim's great insight for less than the price of a set of plans.<P>I think Jim's insight into choosing a boat to build is the best part of the book. If you are thinking about getting a boat or not happy with your boating exerience to date you should buy this book and read that section a few times.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">Never built a small boat before ? This is THE book.</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
